---
// connectionless-vs-pooled — Chapter 074 Lesson 2,
// "The connectionless client: Redis over HTTP".
//
// The lesson's surprise for anyone who has used `pg` / `ioredis`: there is no
// connection pool. This figure makes that answer ITSELF by geometry — two
// stacked panels share the same three-column grid so the heavy "Connection
// pool" box on top sits directly above the GAP on the bottom. The absence of
// the pool box IS the lesson, so the bottom-middle cell is a dashed ghost that
// names the gap rather than leaving it blank — "no pool" reads as intentional,
// not as a layout bug.
//
// Plain HTML + CSS per the diagrams index (annotated / colour-coded strip
// shape; deliberately NOT a diagram engine and NOT ArrowDiagram, whose
// LeaderLines can't be relocated into the Figure lightbox). Astro-scoped
// <style>, no LeaderLines → survives the lightbox, so the wrapping <Figure>
// stays expandable. `not-content` on the root plus a `margin: 0` reset on every
// node defeats Starlight's injected prose margins.
//
// Theme-aware chrome via Starlight gray vars (flips light/dark). The pool box is
// the one saturated, heavy element (amber, tinted + shadowed) so it reads as the
// stateful thing you have to manage; the connectionless path stays light. The
// `→` connectors are plain glyphs sized to align with the box rows.
---

<div class="cvp not-content">
	{/* ───────── Panel A: pooled TCP client ───────── */}
	<div class="cvp-panel">
		<div class="cvp-head">
			<span class="cvp-head-title">Pooled TCP client</span>
			<span class="cvp-head-sub">pg, ioredis</span>
		</div>
		<div class="cvp-row">
			<div class="cvp-box cvp-app">App</div>

			<div class="cvp-link" aria-hidden="true">
				<span class="cvp-arrow">→</span>
				<span class="cvp-link-label">borrow / return socket</span>
			</div>

			{/* the heavy, stateful thing you have to manage */}
			<div class="cvp-box cvp-pool">
				<span class="cvp-pool-name">Connection pool</span>
				<span class="cvp-pool-note">N sockets · open / idle / close</span>
			</div>

			<div class="cvp-link" aria-hidden="true">
				<span class="cvp-arrow">→</span>
				<span class="cvp-link-label">persistent TCP</span>
			</div>

			<div class="cvp-box cvp-server">Redis server</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	{/* ───────── Panel B: connectionless ───────── */}
	<div class="cvp-panel">
		<div class="cvp-head">
			<span class="cvp-head-title">Connectionless</span>
			<span class="cvp-head-sub">@upstash/redis</span>
		</div>
		<div class="cvp-row">
			<div class="cvp-box cvp-app">App</div>

			{/* same 5-cell structure as panel A so columns line up: the single hop
			    lands in the first connector slot, the gap in the pool's column. */}
			<div class="cvp-link" aria-hidden="true">
				<span class="cvp-arrow">→</span>
				<span class="cvp-link-label cvp-link-label-strong">
					fetch(url, token)
				</span>
			</div>

			{/* the gap sits exactly under the pool box above — that's the point */}
			<div class="cvp-gap">
				<span class="cvp-gap-text">no pool</span>
				<span class="cvp-gap-note">nothing to keep alive</span>
			</div>

			{/* empty connector cell — no second hop, so the server still lands in
			    the same column as panel A's server */}
			<div class="cvp-link" aria-hidden="true"></div>

			<div class="cvp-box cvp-server">
				<span class="cvp-server-name">Redis server</span>
				<span class="cvp-server-note">HTTP</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<style>
	.cvp {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 18px;
		margin: 0;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	.cvp-panel {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cvp-head {
		display: flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 8px;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-head-title {
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-head-sub {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
		font-size: 0.66rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Shared FIXED 5-column template on both rows so the pool box (panel A) and
	   the gap (panel B) land in the SAME middle column — the vertical alignment
	   is what makes the missing pool obvious. App | link | middle | link | server.
	   Fixed widths (not auto/1fr) so the two independent grids line up exactly. */
	.cvp-row {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 5rem 8rem 13rem 8rem 5rem;
		justify-content: center;
		align-items: stretch;
		gap: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cvp-box {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 2px;
		padding: 12px 16px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, transparent);
		font-size: 0.84rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* the heavy, stateful node — the whole thing panel B is missing */
	.cvp-pool {
		border: 1.5px solid #b45309; /* amber-700 */
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #f59e0b 22%, transparent);
		box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(180, 83, 9, 0.28);
		padding: 12px 18px;
	}
	.cvp-pool-name {
		font-size: 0.84rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-pool-note {
		font-size: 0.62rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.cvp-server-name {
		font-size: 0.84rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-server-note {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
		font-size: 0.6rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* connectors: arrow + a small label stacked under it */
	.cvp-link {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 2px;
		padding: 0 6px;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-arrow {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-link-label {
		font-size: 0.6rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-link-label-strong {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
	}

	/* the deliberate gap where the pool would be — dashed, muted, labelled */
	.cvp-gap {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 2px;
		padding: 12px 18px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1.5px dashed var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		background: transparent;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-gap-text {
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.cvp-gap-note {
		font-size: 0.6rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* narrow viewports: stack each row, rotate arrows so the read stays clear.
	   Breakpoint sits above the 39rem fixed-grid width so it never overflows. */
	@media (max-width: 680px) {
		.cvp-row {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 4px;
		}
		.cvp-arrow {
			transform: rotate(90deg);
			display: block;
		}
		.cvp-link {
			padding: 2px 0;
		}
	}
</style>
